    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - BODY FEATURES - PARK BRAKE SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08290141">
        <title>PARK BRAKE SWITCH</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <figure id="f08290943" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/G08290943.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Park Brake Switch Function Diagram</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. PARK BRAKE SWITCH</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. ELECTRONIC SYSTEM CONTROLLER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. DRIVE TRAIN 1939 DATA LINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER (EGC)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>There is no park brake switch if the vehicle is equipped with the full power brake system
                        option.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>The ESC uses the park brake switch input for the following functions:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>To determine when to turn on the park lamp on the EGC.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To turn off the daytime running lights when the headlights are off, the engine is not running
                        and the key is in the ignition position.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>To enable the diagnostic trouble code retrieval procedure.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Used as an input to generate the command to the transmission controller to shift to neutral
                        (used with auto neutral feature only).
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
